<p>What is the length of the unmeasured side of the triangle? <fillin characters="20" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.8</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{4.78}^{{2}}={7.52}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{22.8484}={56.5504}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={56.5504}-{22.8484}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={33.702}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{33.702}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{5.8}</m>.</p>
</solution>
